The paper proposes a new neural network architecture for learning set-equivariant functions, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the use of gated recurrent networks and their application to different domains, which suggests a focus on deep learning and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
